OL,3,CGuernsey States' latest accounts show
OL,4,C#63 million net surplus
OL,6,FStates made a net surplus of more than
OL,7,F#63 million in 2023, compared to a net
OL,8,Fdeficit of nearly #140 million the
OL,9,Fprevious year.
OL,11,FLatest accounts show the overall
OL,12,Fpositive impact of cost controls on
OL,13,Ffinances with Health and Social Care a
OL,14,Fclear outlier as its total spend
OL,15,Fincreased by #14.7 million.
OL,17,FThis was driven by rising staffing
OL,18,Fcosts in areas such as agency workers
OL,19,Fand overtime to keep up with the
OL,20,Fgrowing demand for services.
